<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto p-8">
  <div class="text-center">
    <div class="text-6xl mb-6">🏝️</div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-4">IslandJS Rails</h1>
    <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 mb-8">
      Seamlessly integrate React components into your Rails application<br>
      with Turbo-compatible state persistence
    </p>
  </div>

  <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-lg p-8 mb-8">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">🚀 What is IslandJS Rails?</h2>
    <div class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
      <p>
        <strong>IslandJS Rails</strong> allows you to create interactive "islands" of JavaScript 
        within your server-rendered Rails application. Think of it as the perfect balance between 
        SSR and SPA - you get the SEO benefits and fast initial page loads of server-side rendering, 
        with the interactivity of React components exactly where you need them.
      </p>
      <p>
        The real magic happens with <strong>Turbo Cache compatibility</strong> - your React component 
        state persists across page navigation, creating a smooth, app-like experience while maintaining 
        the simplicity of traditional Rails development.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">✨ Key Features</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li>• Server-side rendering with client-side hydration</li>
        <li>• Turbo-compatible state persistence</li>
        <li>• Zero-config React component mounting</li>
        <li>• Automatic CDN loading for dependencies</li>
        <li>• Works with Rails' asset pipeline</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-lg border p-6">
      <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-3">🎯 Perfect For</h3>
      <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-600">
        <li>• Adding interactivity to specific pages</li>
        <li>• Complex forms and widgets</li>
        <li>• Data visualization components</li>
        <li>• Real-time features</li>
        <li>• Progressive enhancement</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="text-center">
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-4">Ready to see it in action?</h3>
    <%= link_to "🧪 Try the React Demo", "/islandjs/react", 
        class: "inline-block bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-semibold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg transition-colors duration-200" %>
    <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-3">
      Interact with the component, then navigate back here to see state persistence in action!
    </p>
  </div>
</div> 